**Section 1 - User Story**

**1.1. Epic Story**

As a Notice Processing Officer who needs to follow up against notices in the OCMS, I want the OCMS to allow me to reduce the composition amount of notices, so that the offender can pay a lower rate at the payment channels.

**1.2. User Stories**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- **Key Functions &amp; Features**

| Functions | Description |
| --- | --- |
| Reduction Initiated by PLUS | When an appeal for a fee reduction is approved by PLUS Officers, the PLUS system sends a request to OCMS to apply the reduced composition amount to the Notice and initiate the reduction. |
| Reduction Process in OCMS Backend | OCMS backend validates the notice by checking the payment status and the last processing stage, and if eligible, applies a reduction to the notice’s composition amount. |

**Section 2 - Reduction Initiated by PLUS**

**2.1 Use case**

1. A Reduction refers to the scenario where PLUS triggers a request to OCMS to reduce the composition amount of the notice.

2. This occurs after PLUS officers review the appeal and determine that the notice qualifies for a reduction.

3. The PLUS system will perform validation to decide whether a Notice is eligible for a Reduction

before the reduction request is sent to the OCMS Intranet Backend.

4. When the OCMS Intranet Backend receives a reduction request, it performs the following actions:

- Verifies whether the notice has been paid to determine if a reduction is required.
- Check Computer rule code: If the computer rule code is 30305/31302/30302/21300, composition amount can be reduced at NPA/ROV/ENA/RD1/RD2/RR3/DN1/DN2/DR3 stage.
- Checks that the last processing stage of the notice is **RR3/DR3 **if the computer rule code is not 30305/31302/30302/21300, as only these stages are eligible for reduction.
- Updates the notice’s payable amount with the reduced amount and suspends the Notice with TS-RED.
Note:

- For MVP1, users have confirmed that the reduction process will be fully managed within the PLUS system, while the OCMS backend will only be responsible for updating the notice with the data provided in the reduction request.

- For MVP1, manual reduction can only be performed from the PLUS system.

**2.4 Processing of Reduction in OCMS Backend**

*Refer to Section 3 – Reduction Process in OCMS Backend*

**Section 3 - Reduction Process in OCMS Backend**

**3.1 Use case**

- The OCMS backend performs the reduction process when it receives a reduction request from the PLUS system via API through APIM.

- OCMS validates the request format and mandatory fields to ensure the data is complete and correct.

- OCMS verifies whether the notice has already been paid. If it has been paid, OCMS responds to PLUS that the notice has been paid and the reduction is not applicable.

- If the notice is outstanding, OCMS checks the last processing stage. Only notices at **RR3/DR3** are eligible for reduction.

- If the notice is eligible, OCMS updates the notice with the reduced payable amount provided in the request and suspends the notice with a temporary suspension reason ‘**RED’**.**
**
- OCMS returns a response to PLUS indicating whether the reduction was successfully applied or if it failed (e.g., due to update failure or system error).
Note:

- OCMS will follow PLUS’s confirmation and reject any reduction request for paid notices.

- Reduction of notices can be performed at the RR3/DR3 stage and at court stages from CFC to CWT. For MVP1, only the RR3/DR3 stage is included. Reductions at the court stages are not implemented at this stage, but they remain within the overall reduction scope and will be discussed after MVP1.
**3.2 Process Flow
**

**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

NOTE: Due to page size limit, the full-sized image is appended.

**![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)**

| No. | Process | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Start | PLUS System sends a request to OCMS Intranet Backend for Reduction via API. |
| 2 | OCMS Receives Request | OCMS Intranet Backend receives the request routed through APIM. |
| 3 | Validate Request Format | OCMS checks if the API request data is complete and valid. If the request is invalid, OCMS responds to PLUS with "Invalid format" and ends the process. If the format is valid, OCMS proceeds to Step 4. |
| 4 | Check for Mandatory Data | OCMS checks whether all required fields are present. If data is missing, OCMS responds to PLUS with "Missing data" and ends the process. If the mandatory data is present, OCMS proceeds to Step 5. |
| 5 | Check if Notice has been paid | OCMS checks the CRS Reason of Suspension field to detect if it is blank or has a null value (i.e. notice has not been paid) If the CRS Reason of Suspension field is blank or null, this indicates that the Notice is outstanding. OCMS proceeds to Step 6 to check the last processing stage of notice. If the CRS Reason of Suspension field value is either “FP” or “PRA”, this indicates that payment has been made. OCMS responds to PLUS that the notice has been paid. |
| 6 | Check Computer Rule Code is eligible | If a notice remains outstanding, OCMS validates whether the notice’s computer rule code matches any of the Eligible Computer Rule Codes (30305, 31302, 30302, 21300). (a) If the notice’s computer rule code is among the Eligible Computer Rule Codes, OCMS allows reduction at stages NPA/ROV/ENA/RD1/RD2/RR3/DN1/DN2/DR3 and then proceeds to Step 8 to update the notice payment data for reduction. (b) If the notice’s computer rule code does not match any of the Eligible Computer Rule Codes, OCMS will proceed to check whether the notice’s last processing qualifies for reduction. |
| 7 | Check Last Processing Stage | If the notice’s computer rule codes is not among the eligible computer rule codes, OCMS validates the notice’s last processing stage. Only notices at RR3/DR3 stage are eligible for reduction. If the notice is not at RR3/DR3 stage, OCMS responds to PLUS that the reduction fail and the process ends. If the notice last process stage is at RR3/DR3, it proceed to reduce the composition amount of the notice. If the notice last process stage is not at RR3/DR3, the reduction request is not eligible and OCMS responds to PLUS that Notice’s processing stage is not eligible for Reduction. |
| 8 | Update Notice Payment data | OCMS updates the amount payable field in ocms_valid_offence_notice table. The update is made to the Intranet and Internet database tables. |
| 9 | Notice is suspended with TS-RED | OCMS suspends the notice with the temporary suspension reason ‘RED’, updates the suspension data in the ocms_valid_offence_notice table, and adds a suspension record to the ocms_suspended_notice table. |
| 10 | Was the Update Successful? | System checks if the update to notice was successful. If the update was unsuccessful, OCMS responds to PLUS with "Reduction Fail" and ends the process. If the update was successful, OCMS responds to PLUS with "Reduction Success" and ends the process. |

**3.3 Reduction Scenarios and Outcomes
**

- The table below lists the possible scenarios and outcomes that may occur and how OCMS will handle each scenario: 

| Scenario | Description | Outcome | Handling |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Invalid Request Format | Request received by OCMS from PLUS is incomplete or has invalid structure. | Rejected by OCMS | Respond to PLUS with “Invalid format” and end processing. |
| Missing Mandatory Data | Request has mandatory data fields. | Rejected by OCMS | Respond to PLUS with “Missing data” and end processing. |
| Notice has been paid | The notice has already been fully paid. | Rejected by OCMS | Respond to PLUS with “Notice has been paid” and end processing. |
| Notice is not eligible | The notice’s computer rule code is not 30305/ 31302/ 30302/ 21300 and the last-processing stage is at NPA/ROV/ENA/RD1/RD2/DN1/DN2. | Rejected by OCMS | Respond to PLUS with “Notice is not eligible” and end processing. |
| Successful Update | Request is valid and contains all required data. OCMS updates the Notice and adds suspension code. | Notice updated and suspended successfully | Respond to PLUS with “Reduction success” and end processing. |
| Update Failure | Request passes validation and data checks, but the update fails internally (e.g. DB error). | Update unsuccessful | Respond to PLUS with “Reduction fail” and end processing. |
| Backend System Unavailable | OCMS can’t access the database or system error. | Update fails | Respond to PLUS with “System unavailable” error and end processing |
| Partial Update | Data updated but suspension record creation fails. | Incomplete processing | Implement rollback of updates Respond to PLUS with “Reduction fail” End processing |

**3.4 Attributes of a Reduction Notice
**

**3.4.1 Saving Reduction Notice data to the Intranet and Internet databases 
 **

- When a Reduction request is successful, OCMS will update the notice details in the following database tables in the Intranet and Internet:

| Zone | Database Table Name |
| --- | --- |
| Intranet | ocms_valid_offence_notice (also referred to as VON table) ocms_suspended_notice ocms_reduced_offence_amount |
| Internet | eocms_valid_offence_notice (also referred to as eVON table) eocms_suspended_notice |

- Fields to be updated in the Intranet ocms_valid_offence_notice and Internet eocms_valid_offence_notice database are:

| Field Name | Description | Sample Value |
| --- | --- | --- |
| amount_payable | The amount after reduction is granted | 70.00 |
| suspension_type | Type of suspension | TS |
| epr_reason_of_suspension | EPR reason of suspension | RED |
| epr_reason_suspension_date | Date and time the suspension was applied | 2025-08-01 19:00:02 |
| due_date_of_revival | Date and time the suspension will expire | 2025-08-15 00:00:00 |
| upd_date | Update date | 2025-08-01 19:00:02 |
| upd_user_id | User ID who updated the record | JOHNLEE |

**3.4.2 Creating Suspended Notice record in the Intranet database
**

When a Reduction request is successful, OCMS will apply temporary suspensions to the Notice with suspension reason ‘RED’.

| Field Name | Description | Sample Value |
| --- | --- | --- |
| notice_no* | Notice number | 500500303J |
| date_of_suspension* | Date the suspension was applied | 2025-08-01 19:00:02 |
| sr_no* | Serial number for suspension, running number | 1 |
| suspension_source* | Which system initiated the suspension | PLUS |
| suspension_type* | Type of suspension | TS |
| reason_of_suspension* | EPR suspension code that indicates the reason for the suspension | ‘RED’ – Pay Reduced Amount |
| officer_authorising_suspension* | Name of Officer who initiated the suspension | {{cre_user_id}} from PLUS’s reduction request |
| due_date_of_revival | Date when the Suspension will be lifted. | 2025-08-15 00:00:00 |
| suspension_remarks | Suspension remarks entered by the Officer who initiated the Suspension | {{reason of reduction} from PLUS’s reduction request |

**3.4.3 Add Reduction record to reduced_offence_amount** **table in the Intranet database**

**
**Note: This reduced_offence_amount table follows the CAS, and the purpose of this table is to log the reduction records.
